news.title: Cement industry growth to slow down to 7-8% to 475 MT in FY25: Report
news.para: ​​The cement demand grew only 3 per cent in the June first quarter of FY2024-25, owing to an extended heatwave and shortage of labour during general elections and is estimated to have grown at a similar pace in the second quarter due to seasonal weakness.

news.title: Delhi HC asks CBI to file status report on DHFL ex-director's bail plea
news.para: Justice Chandra Dhari Singh asked the CBI to file within 10 days its status report on various aspects, including its objections raised on the maintainability of the petition.

news.title: Bombay HC overturns Bank of India's fraud declaration against Pune Buildtech
news.para: In another separate order, the court has also directed the lender to remove the company’s name from the list of ‘wilful defaulters’ and has also directed the bank to recall any information sent by it to any Credit Information Company declaring Pune Buildtech as wilful defaulters.

news.title: Sattva Group partners with Bain Capital to develop co-living platform
news.para: The platform will be housed under Colive, a company that manages rental homes, they said, adding that this is the largest funding received so far by a coliving platform to develop a built-to-suit co-living asset.

news.title: Real estate equity investment reaches $8.9 billion in Jan-Sept 2024: Report
news.para: On a quarterly basis, equity investments in real estate stood at $2.6 billion in Q2 FY25.

news.title: Issued final notifications to enforce fire safety norms for vulnerable buildings: Maharashtra government
news.para: The notification would include security rules in Development Control and Promotion Regulations (DCPR), 2034, for Greater Mumbai and Unified Development Control And Promotion Regulations (UDCPR) for the rest of the state.

news.title: Goa: Residents of Betalbatim oppose mega construction projects
news.para: ​Pointing to a number of people from outside Goa investing in properties in the village, which were later sold at exorbitant prices, villagers asserted that they would not allow their land to be used for mega construction projects.

news.title: Bajaj housing finance shares drop 4% as one month lock-in period expires on October 14
news.para: This means that approximately 12.6 crore (126 million) shares of the company, which were previously locked in and prohibited from sale, will now be eligible to be sold.

news.title: China to introduce new measures to support property sector
news.para: ​​Lan hinted at room for issuing more sovereign bonds and vowed to relieve the debt burden of local governments, signaling a possible rare revision to the budget that could come in the next few weeks.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout owners stuck as BDA delays collecting betterment charges
news.para: They said that paying betterment charges will help residents and investors get “A” khata from the present “gramathana” site or revenue site status. Revenue sites are considered illegal, hence the owners face many limitations and legal issues.

news.title: ED initiates refund drive for six crore investors in Pearl Group ponzi scam
news.para: The agency said it has shared details of Rs 700 crore worth of attached assets of Pearl Agro Group with Justice Lodha Committee, the panel appointed by Supreme Court to administer disposal of confiscated assets and restitution of funds to the victims.

news.title: Allahabad HC stays Noida authority's construction ban on Satya Homes
news.para: The Authority rejected the application the very next day, saying the land they had bought was part of a notified area that would eventually be acquired for institutional development of Sector 161.

news.title: SC's tax ruling on ITC may boost commercial realty investments
news.para: Offices, malls, and hospitality ventures focused on building and leasing properties are likely to gain the most from the top court ruling as these areas usually require substantial upfront investments and long-term financial commitments.

news.title: ED to interrogate Sahiti Infratec's MD in infra scam probe
news.para: Lakshminarayana, who was arrested on Sept 29 in connection with the scam, will be taken into ED custody from Chanchalaguda jail for questioning and returned on Fri to judicial custody.

news.title: MMRDA to lease out three plots in Mumbai's BKC to generate Rs 656 crore
news.para: The largest of these, located in G Block, covers 52,138 square metre and is designated for the development of a world-class clubhouse and sports facility.

news.title: Goa police to continue verification drive, prosecute renters over unverified tenants
news.para: Director general of police (DGP) Alok Kumar said Goa police is committed to taking all possible steps to provide a safe and secure atmosphere to Goans and tourists who come here in large numbers.

news.title: Maharashtra SCDRC directs Ashtavinayak Developer to pay for 'deficient service'
news.para: Ulwe residents, Vir Bhan Sharma (65) and Disha Sharma (27), moved the commission in 2019 against Dhulchand Naik, proprietor of M/s Ashtavinayak Developer.

news.title: Over 300 flats registered in Noida during Navratri
news.para: Assistant inspector general registration (I) BS Verma said, "Usually, we register 10-20 flats daily. However, we registered three times more than that during Navratri as people see it as an auspicious time for significant purchases. On some days, we registered 75-85 flats in a day."

news.title: Mumbai: EOW closes second case against Nirmal Lifestyle's directors
news.para: Last year, the EOW closed another case against the Jains, including the manager of the Videocon Group, Chandrakant Dhoot, and Venugopal Dhoot. The EOW recently filed a closure report classifying it as ‘C' summary.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra sale bookings rise 1% to Rs 254 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: The sale bookings rose 18 per cent to Rs 560 crore during April-September period of 2024-25 from Rs 476 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing.
